obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34357)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34357&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prisoners Act, 1900;`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^2[the territories which, immediately before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States.] ^3***`
  line
  line ^3*****
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 1 of Act III of 1900.--In the Prisoners Act, 1900, in the application to`
  line `the State of Bombay, in sub-section (2) of section 1, after the words and letter "comprised in Part B`
  line `States" the words "other than the Hyderabad and Saurashtra areas of the State of Bombay" shall be`
  line added.
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XV of 1959, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Bihar by Bihar Act 23 of 1956.`
  line
  line `2. Madras by Madras Act 11 of 1958.`
  line
  line `3.Bombay by Bombay Act 15 of 1959 (when notified).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34358)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34358&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Court" includes a Coroner and any officer lawfully exercising civil, criminal or revenue`
  line `jurisdiction; and`
  line
  line `(b) "prison" includes any place which has been declared by the State Government, by`
  line `general or special order, to be a subsidiary jail.`
  line
  line `^1[(c) "States" means the territories to which this Act extends.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. N.E.P.A. by Reg. 3 of 1960, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line `The Act has been extended to--`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34359)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Officers in charge of prisons to detain persons duly committed to their custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34359&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The officer in charge of a prison shall receive and detain all persons duly committed to his`
  line `custody, under this Act or otherwise, by any Court, according to the exigency of any writ,`
  line `warrant or order by which such person has been committed, or until such person is discharged`
  line `or removed in due course of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34360)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Officers in charge of prisons to return writs, etc., after execution or discharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34360&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line The
  line `officer in charge of a prison shall forthwith, after the execution of every such writ, order or`
  line `warrant as aforesaid other than a warrant of commitment for trial, or after the discharge of the`
  line `person committed thereby, return such writ, order or warrant to the Court by which the same`
  line `was issued or made, together with a certificate, endorsed thereon and signed by him, showing how the same has been executed, or why the person committed thereby has been discharged`
  line `from custody before the execution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34361)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Warrants, etc., to be directed to Police-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34361&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every writ or warrant for the arrest of`
  line `any person issued by the High Court in the exercise of its ordinary, extraordinary or other criminal`
  line `jurisdiction shall be directed to and executed by a Police officer within the local limits of such`
  line jurisdiction.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34362)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power for State Governments to appoint Superintendents of Presidency prisons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34362&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may appoint officers who shall have authority to receive and detain`
  line `prisoners committed to their custody under this part.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Any officer so appointed, by whatever designation he may be styled, is hereinafter`
  line `referred to as "the Superintendent".`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34363)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Delivery of persons sentenced to imprisonment or death by High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34363&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line Where
  line `any person is sentenced by the High Court in the exercise of its original criminal jurisdiction to`
  line `imprisonment or to death, the Court shall cause him to be delivered to the Superintendent together`
  line `with its warrant, and such warrant shall be executed by the Superintendent and returned by him to the`
  line `High Court when executed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34364)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Delivery of persons sentenced to transportation by High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or penal servitude", omitted by Act 17 of 1949. s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34364&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Where any person`
  line `is sentenced by the High Court in the exercise of its original criminal jurisdiction to`
  line `transportation ^1*** the Court shall cause him to be delivered for intermediate custody to the`
  line `Superintendent, and the transportation ^1*** of such person shall be deemed to commence from`
  line `such delivery.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34365)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Delivery of persons committed by High Court in execution of a decree or for contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34365&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Where any person is committed by the High Court, whether in execution of a decree or`
  line `for contempt of Court or for any other cause, the Court shall cause him to be delivered to the`
  line `Superintendent, together with its warrant of commitment.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34366)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Delivery of persons sentenced by Presidency Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34366&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where any person is`
  line `sentenced by a Presidency Magistrate to imprisonment, or is committed to prison for failure to find`
  line `security to keep the peace or to be of good behavior, the Magistrate shall cause him to be delivered to`
  line `the Superintendent, together with his warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34367)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Delivery of persons committed for trial by High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1908, s. 13, for "Justice of the Peace, or Coroner".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34367&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every person committed by`
  line `a Magistrate, ^1[or Justice of the Peace] for trial by the high Court in the exercise of its original`
  line `criminal jurisdiction shall be delivered to the Superintendent, together with a warrant of commitment,`
  line `directing the Superintendent to produce such person before the Court for trial; and the Superintendent`
  line `shall, as soon as practicable, cause such person to be taken before the Court at a criminal session`
  line `thereof, together with the warrant of commitment, in order that he may be dealt with according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34412)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Custody pending hearing by High Court under section 350 of the Code of Civil Procedure of application for insolvency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34412&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, pending the hearing, under`
  line `section 350 of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882), ^1`
  line `of any application for a declaration of`
  line `insolvency, cause the judgment-debtor concerned to be delivered to the Superintendent, subject`
  line `to the provisions as to release on security of ^1`
  line `section 349 of the said Code, and the`
  line `Superintendent shall detain the said judgment-debtor in safe custody until he is re-delivered to`
  line `an officer of the High Court for the purpose of being taken before it in pursuance of its order, or`
  line `until he is released in due course of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. This reference should be constrained as applying to the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920), see s. 83 (2) of that`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34413)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Delivery of persons arrested in pursuance of warrant of High Court or Civil Court in Presidency- town.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34413&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person arrested in pursuance of a writ, warrant or order of the High`
  line `Court in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction, or in pursuance of a warrant of any Civil Court`
  line `established in a Presidency-town under any law or enactment for the time being in force, or in`
  line `pursuance of a warrant issued under section 5, shall be brought without delay before the Court by`
  line `which, or by a Judge of which, the writ, warrant or order was issued, awarded or made, or before a`
  line `Judge thereof, if the said Court, or a Judge thereof is then sitting for the exercise of original`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(2) If the said Court, or a Judge thereof, is not then sitting for the exercise of original jurisdiction,`
  line `such person arrested as aforesaid shall, unless a Judge of the said Court otherwise directs, be delivered`
  line `to the Superintendent for intermediate custody, and shall be brought before the said Court, or a Judge`
  line `thereof, at the next sitting of the said Court, or of a Judge thereof, for the exercise of original`
  line `jurisdiction in order that such person may be dealt with according to law; and the said Court or Judge`
  line `shall have power to make or award all necessary orders or warrants for that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34370)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `References in this Part to prisons, etc., to be construed as referring also to Reformatory Schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34370&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `In this Part all references to prisons or to imprisonment or confinement`
  line `shall be construed as referring also to Reformatory Schools or to detention therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34371)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power for officers in charge of prisons to give effect to sentences of certain Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34371&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1 [15. Power for officers in charge of prisons to give effect to sentences of certain`
  line `Courts.-- (1) Officers in charge of prisons outside the Presidency towns may give effect to any`
  line `sentence or order or warrant for the detention of any person passed or issued`
  line
  line `(a) by any Court or tribunal acting, whether within or without the States under the`
  line `general or special authority of the Central Government, or of any State Government, or`
  line `of the Government of Burma, or by any Court or tribunal, which was before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution acting under the general or special authority of His`
  line `Majesty, or of the Crown Representative; or`
  line
  line `(b) before the 26th January, 1950, by any Court or tribunal in any Indian State--`
  line
  line `(i) if the presiding Judge, or if the Court or tribunal consisted of two or more Judges,`
  line `at least one of the Judges, was an officer of the Crown authorised to sit as such Judge`
  line `by the State or the Ruler thereof or by the Central Government or the Crown`
  line `Representative; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if the reception, detention or imprisonment in any Province of India of persons`
  line `sentenced by any such Court or tribunal had been authorised by general or special`
  line `order by the State Government : or`
  line
  line `^2** * * *`
  line
  line `Provided that effect shall not be given to any sentence or order or warrant for detention passed or`
  line `issued by any Court or tribunal in Burma without the previous sanction of the State Government`
  line concerned.
  line
  line `(2) Where a Court or tribunal of such an Indian State as aforesaid had passed a sentence`
  line `which could not have been executed without the concurrence of an officer of the Crown,`
  line `and such sentence had been considered on the merits and confirmed by any such officer`
  line `specially authorised in that behalf, such sentence, and any order or warrant issued in`
  line `pursuance thereof, shall be deemed to be the sentence, order or warrant of a Court or`
  line `tribunal acting under the authority of the Central Government or the Crown`
  line `Representative.)`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for section 15.`
  line
  line `2. Clause (c) omitted The Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34372)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Warrant of officer of such Court to be sufficient authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34372&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `A warrant under the`
  line `official signature of an officer of such Court or tribunal as is referred to in section 15 shall be`
  line `sufficient authority for holding any person in confinement, or for sending any person for`
  line `transportation, in pursuance of the sentence passed upon him.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34414)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Procedure where officer in charge of prison doubts the legality of warrant sent to him for execution under this Part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34414&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an officer in charge of a prison doubts the legality`
  line `of a warrant or order sent to him for execution under this Part, or the competency of the person whose`
  line `official seal or signature is affixed thereto to pass the sentence and issue the warrant or order, he shall`
  line `refer the matter to the State Government, by whose order on the case he and all other public officers`
  line `shall be guided as to the future disposal of the prisoner.`
  line
  line `(2) Pending a reference made under sub-section (1), the prisoner shall be detained in such manner`
  line `and with such restrictions or mitigations as may be specified in the warrant or order.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34374)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Execution in the States of certain capital sentences not ordinarily executable there.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34374&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a ^1[Court established by the authority of the Central Government] exercising, in`
  line `or with respect to territory beyond the limits of the States, jurisdiction which ^2[the ^3[Central`
  line `Government]] has in such territory--,`
  line
  line `(a) has sentenced any person to death, and`
  line
  line `(b) being of opinion that such sentence should, by reason of there being in such territory no`
  line `secure place for the confinement of such person or no suitable appliances for his execution in a`
  line `decent and humane manner, be executed in the States has issued its warrant for the execution of`
  line `such sentence to the officer in charge of a prison in the States,`
  line
  line `such officer shall, on receipt of the warrant, cause the execution to be carried out at such place as may`
  line `be prescribed therein in the same manner and subject to the same conditions in all respects as if it`
  line `were a warrant duly issued under the provisions of section 381 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1898 (5 of 1898).`
  line
  line `(2) The prisons of which the officers in charge are to execute sentences under any such warrants as aforesaid ^4[shall in each State be such as the State Government] may, by general or special order,`
  line direct.
  line
  line ^5*****
