obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (34384)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `References in this Part to prisons, etc., to be construed as referring also to Reformatory Schools.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34384&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `In this Part, all references to prisons or to imprisonment or confinement`
  line `shall be construed as referring also to Reformatory Schools or to detention therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (34385)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Removal of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34385&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[29. Removal of prisoners.—(1) The ^2`
  line `[State Government] may, by general or special order.`
  line `provide for the removal of any prisoner confined in a prison—`
  line
  line `(a) under sentence of death, or`
  line
  line `(b) under, or in lieu of, a sentence of imprisonment or transportation, or`
  line
  line `(c) in default of payment of a fine, or`
  line
  line `(d) in default of giving security for keeping the peace or for maintaining good behavior,`
  line `to any other prison in ^3`
  line `[the State ^4`
  line ***].
  line
  line `(2) ^5`
  line `[Subject to the orders, and under the control, of the State Government] the Inspector-General`
  line `of Prisons may, in like manner, provide for the removal of any prisoner confined as aforesaid in a`
  line `prison in the State to any other prison in the State`
  line ^6
  line .]
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1903, s. 3 and the second Schedule for section 29.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "G. G. in C.".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "British India or to any prison in Berar". The words "or to any prison in Berar" had been`
  line `added by Act 17 of 1923. s. 2.`
  line
  line `4. The words "or, with the consent of the State Government concerned, to any prison in any other State" omitted by Act 29`
  line `of 1950, s. 4.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "The L. G., and (subject to its orders and under its control)".`
  line
  line `6. The words "or, in the case of prisoner so confined in a prison in the C. P., for his removal to any other prison in the`
  line `Province or to any prison in Berar", which had been added by Act 17 of 1923, s. 2 were omitted by the A. O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (34386)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Lunatic prisoners how to be dealt with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591&sectionId=34386&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00018_190003_1523339448591
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the State Government`
  line `that any person detained or imprisoned under any order or sentence of any Court is of unsound mind,`
  line `the State Government may, by a warrant setting forth the grounds of belief that the person is of`
  line `unsound mind, order his removal to a lunatic asylum or other place of safe custody within the State,`
  line `there to be kept and treated as the State Government directs during the remainder of the term for`
  line `which he has been ordered or sentenced to be detained or imprisoned, or, if on the expiration of that`
  line `term it is certified by a medical officer that it is necessary for the safety of the prisoner or others that`
  line `he should be further detained under medical care or treatment, then until he is discharged according to`
  line law.
  line
  line `(2) Where it appears to the State Government that the prisoner has become of sound mind, the`
  line `State Government shall, by a warrant directed to the person having charge of the prisoner, if still`
  line `liable to be kept in custody, remand him to the prison from which he was removed, or to another`
  line `prison within the State, or, if the prisoner is no longer liable to be kept in custody, order him to be`
  line discharged.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 9 of the ^1Lunatic Asylums Act, 1858 (36 of 1858), shall apply to every person confined in a lunatic asylum under sub-section (1) after the expiration of`
  line `the term for which he was ordered or sentenced to be detained or imprisoned, and the time during`
  line `which a prisoner is confined in a lunatic asylum under that sub-section shall he reckoned as part`
  line `of the term of detention or imprisonment which he may have been ordered or sentenced by the`
  line `Court to undergo.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(4) In any case in which the State Government is competent under sub-section (1) to order`
  line `the removal of a prisoner to a lunatic asylum or other place of safe custody within the State, the`
  line `State Government may order his removal to any such asylum or place within any other State or`
  line `within ^3`
  line `[any part of India to which this Act does not extend] by agreement with the State`
  line `Government of such other State^4`
  line `***; and the provisions of this section respecting the custody,`
  line `detention, remand and discharge of a prisoner removed under sub-section (1) shall, so far as they`
  line `can be made applicable apply to a prisoner removed under this sub-section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Indian Lunacy Act, 1912 (4 of 1912).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "any Part B State".`
  line
  line `4. The words “or with such State or the Ruler thereof, as the case may be” omitted, ibid.`
